Salesforce MCP + Claude Code Integration Guide
1. Overview
Section	Details
Integration	This guide describes how Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) integrates with Claude Code using the Model Context Protocol (MCP).
Transport	The integration communicates over HTTP.
Auth Method	Authentication uses OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code flow with PKCE (S256) for added security.
Client Type	The implementation uses a public package, so no client secret is required.
Token Lifetime	Access tokens remain valid for approximately 18 minutes, and refresh tokens are not used.
Scope	The integration is scoped at the project level and is active only within the designated project directory.


2. Prerequisites
•	A Salesforce Marketing Cloud account with admin access to Setup → Apps → Installed Packages
•	An Installed Package configured as:
•	Package type: Public (no client secret)
•	Grant type: Authorization Code
•	Claude Code installed on Windows (AppData\Roaming\Claude\claude-code\<version>\claude.exe)
•	PowerShell 5.1+ for running the refresh script
•	A modern browser for the OAuth login flow

3. Gathering Your SFMC Endpoints
•	Navigate to SFMC Setup → Apps → Installed Packages and open your package
•	Record the following values:
Endpoint	Format
MCP URL	https://mai-mce-mcp-cdp1.sfdc-yfeipo.svc.sfdcfc.net/t/<TENANT_ID>/c/<ROUTING_ID>/api/mcp
REST Base	https://<TENANT_ID>.rest.marketingcloudapis.com
Auth Base	https://<TENANT_ID>.auth.marketingcloudapis.com
SFMC Login	https://mc.login.exacttarget.com/hub-cas/login
•	Note: the <ROUTING_ID> in the MCP URL is not the OAuth client ID — a new client is dynamically registered during each token refresh

4. OAuth Discovery Endpoints
•	The MCP server publishes standard OAuth metadata at these well-known URLs:
Purpose	Endpoint
Client Registration	{MCP_URL}/register
Authorization	{MCP_URL}/authorize
Token Exchange	{MCP_URL}/token
Protected Resource Metadata	{MCP_SERVER}/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource/t/<TENANT>/c/<CLIENT>/api/mcp
Auth Server Metadata	{AUTH_SERVER}/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server


5. Authentication Flow (Step-by-Step)
    The entire flow is automated by the refresh script, but here is what happens under the hood:
    1.	Dynamic Client Registration
    •	Script sends POST {MCP_URL}/register to obtain a fresh OAuth client ID
    2.	PKCE Challenge Generation
    •	A random code_verifier is generated
    •	A code_challenge is derived using SHA-256 (S256 method)
    3.	Local HTTP Listener
    •	Script starts a listener on localhost:54322 to capture the callback
    4.	Browser Authorization
    •	Script opens {MCP_URL}/authorize in the browser
    •	MCP server redirects to SFMC login (mc.login.exacttarget.com)
    •	If an active SFMC session exists, login completes silently (no manual input)
    5.	Callback Capture
    •	SFMC redirects back through MCP to localhost:54322/callback?code=...
    •	Script captures the authorization code
    6.	Token Exchange
    •	Script sends POST {MCP_URL}/token with the code + code_verifier
    •	Receives a Bearer token valid for ~18 minutes

    7.	Claude Code MCP Registration
    •	Script removes the old MCP entry and re-adds with the fresh token:
      1.	claude mcp remove salesforce-mcp
      2.	claude mcp add --transport http salesforce-mcp {MCP_URL} --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    8.	Connection Verified
    •	MCP server shows: Connected
    9.	
6. Important Auth Constraints
    Constraint	Detail
    Client Credentials flow	Not supported — will fail with invalid_client on public packages.
    Refresh tokens	Not issued — full PKCE re-authentication is required every cycle.
    SFMC browser session	Must remain active for silent refresh; if it expires, manual login is required.
    PKCE method	Only S256 is accepted.

7. Automating Token Refresh (Windows Scheduled Task)
Since tokens expire every ~18 minutes and no refresh tokens exist, a scheduled task keeps the connection alive.
Task Configuration
Setting	Value
Task Name	SFMC-MCP-TokenRefresh
Task Path	\ClaudeCode\
Frequency	Every 15 minutes
Script	C:\Users\<user>\.claude\sfmc-refresh.ps1
Execution Policy	Bypass
Window Style	Hidden

Management Commands
•	Trigger a manual refresh:
Start-ScheduledTask -TaskPath "\ClaudeCode\" -TaskName "SFMC-MCP-TokenRefresh"
•	View refresh logs:
Get-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.claude\sfmc-refresh.log"
•	Disable the scheduled task:
Disable-ScheduledTask -TaskPath "\ClaudeCode\" -TaskName "SFMC-MCP-TokenRefresh"
•	Enable the scheduled task:
Enable-ScheduledTask -TaskPath "\ClaudeCode\" -TaskName "SFMC-MCP-TokenRefresh"
•	Manual re-auth (if the task fails or session expired):
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "$env:USERPROFILE\.claude\sfmc-refresh.ps1"

8. Verifying the Connection
•	Run the following to confirm the MCP server is active:
claude mcp list
•	Expected output should show salesforce-mcp as connected
•	If the server shows disconnected or returns 401 errors, re-run the refresh script manually

9. Files Created During Setup
File	Purpose
~/.claude/sfmc-refresh.ps1	Full OAuth PKCE refresh script that handles registration, authorization, token exchange, and MCP re-registration.
~/.claude/sfmc-refresh.log	Log output from each refresh cycle.
~/.claude.json	Main Claude Code configuration file containing the salesforce-mcp server entry with the current bearer token.
