10. Features Available via the Salesforce MCP Layer
Once connected, Claude Code can perform SFMC operations conversationally through the MCP bridge. You describe what you need in plain English, and Claude translates it into the correct SFMC REST API calls.
Data Extension Management
Capability	API Endpoint	What Claude Can Do
List DEs	GET /data/v1/customobjects	List all Data Extensions in the account
Create DEs	POST /data/v1/customobjects	Create new DEs with full field schemas
Update DEs	PATCH /data/v1/customobjects/{id}	Modify DE properties including sendable config
Inspect DE Fields	GET /data/v1/customobjects/{id}/fields	Read the full field schema of any DE

Folder Navigation
Capability	API Endpoint	What Claude Can Do
Folder Details	GET /email/v1/categories/{id}	Look up any SFMC folder by category ID
Folder Tree	Walk via parentCatId	Build full folder paths (e.g., Data Extensions > Subfolder > DE Name)
Filter by Type	GET /email/v1/categories?$filter=categorytype eq 'dataextension'	List all Data Extension folders
Automations
Capability	API Endpoint	What Claude Can Do
List Automations	GET /automation/v1/automations	Retrieve all automations and their statuses
Check Status	Status field in response	Identify active automations (Ready = active)
Sendable Data Extension Setup
•	Claude handles the two-step creation flow automatically:
•	Step 1 — Create the DE with isSendable: false
•	Step 2 — PATCH to enable sendable config using string-form fields
•	This avoids the known JSON deserialization bug when passing sendableSubscriberField as an object

11. SFMC REST API Quirks (Auto-Handled by Claude)
These undocumented quirks caused repeated failures during the POC. Claude applies them automatically when operating through the MCP layer.
Quirk	Details
length vs maxLength	Problem: maxLength is silently ignored, and the API reports that no length was specified.
Correct approach: Always use length (for example, "length": 100).
EmailAddress requires length	Problem: The error says the length is "invalid," but it actually means the value is required.
Correct approach: Always pass "length": 254 for EmailAddress fields.
Sendable field as string	Problem: Using the object form {"name": "..."} causes a deserialization error.
Correct approach: Use plain strings, for example: "sendableSubscriberField": "Subscriber Key".
All booleans required	Problem: Omitting any boolean returns the error "isTemplateField is required."
Correct approach: Include all of the following: isTemplateField, isHidden, isOverridable, isInheritable, isReadOnly, mustOverride, and isNullable.
categoryId required	Problem: Data Extension creation fails without a folder reference.
Correct approach: Look up the folder first using /email/v1/categories/{id} before creating the Data Extension.


12. Known Limitations
•	No refresh tokens — every ~18 minutes a full PKCE re-auth is required (automated via scheduled task)
•	Browser opens briefly during each refresh cycle to complete the OAuth callback; it auto-closes
•	Active SFMC session required — if the browser session expires, the next refresh will prompt for manual login
•	Project-scoped only — the salesforce-mcp server is registered at the project level and is only active inside the designated project directory
•	Port conflicts — the OAuth callback listener uses localhost:54322; if this port is occupied, the refresh will fail (update the port in the script)


